      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PRIORITISE (1) has been about the money of late and again performed admirably last time out, making up plenty of ground but finding one marginally better over 1790m at this track. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Meets a comparable field and he can grab that well-deserved win. ALL DA RAGE (3) finished seventh last start over 1790m here, beaten 17 metres, after scoring at the previous appearance over 1800m at Globe Derby Park. Has the benefit of a good draw and rates a big chance if things go his way. MY ULTIMATE JIMMY NZ (6) finished ninth last start over 2690m at Maryborough. Generally runs very well at this circuit so can play a big role. SANTA CASA BEACH (2) is worth some thought despite his last-start seventh over 1790m at this venue on May 15. Can improve from the low draw.",
